Welcome
to CaddyBytes.com?s Tournament's page for
the  2011 Tiger Woods Chevron World Challenge  -formerly Target World
Challenge golf tournament.  The Tiger Woods Chevron World Challenge is
played at the Sherwood Country Club in Thousand Oaks, California.    
 
The
annual format is that sixteen of the world's best golfers compete in a 72 hole
stroke play event.  The field is comprised of the top eleven players from
the World Golf Ranking as of September 30, 2011.  (Who accept invitations
to play).   
 
The Tiger Woods Foundation is the primary charitable recipient of this exclusive
year end event founded by Tiger. 
 
 The defending champion, Jim Furyk, from last year's tourney automatically
qualifies to play as well as four picks to be determined by the Tiger Woods
Foundation whom the tournament primarily benefits.  
 
 Tiger is back this year and the Chevron Challenge is now an official event
where performance in this tournament counts with regard to participant world
ranking.  The tournament is being played earlier this year in a down
economy and no Skins Game and coinciding with Tour School the week of November
28th - December 4th 2011. 
 
